		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=88837"><span id=>Carrbunkle</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>21 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.45]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Carrbunkle&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>We are tanks, not as good as warriors, but with our spells we can easily taunt nearly nething off of a caster, and that is our role in a group. Besides we were made to be able to solo, and thats what you should do. besides, to me, my monk got extremely boring at higher lvls, because after a little while, your charecter basically stops growing(no new techniques, etc.) and they only get AC and HP. I play an SK becuase they continually grow and become stronger, with better spells etc. And dueling, the only duel ive lost is from a higher lvl monk(very twinked, trance sticks etc) when i was around lvl 10, otherwise ive won about 15 other duels, and lemme tell ya, SKs rule at soloing, better than any class in my opinion, and even tho i didn't really answer any of ur questions, I hope this helps you.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Carrbunkle Darrkblade<br>Berrtoxolous Server</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sun, Sep 2nd 10:06 PM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=9994037734312&num=3&post=1&replyto=99948277526883"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=99948277526883></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.66]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Ok I concur that we are tanks with somewhat less hit points and depending on equipment than warriors.&nbsp;&nbsp;But really what you do at the higher levels is dependant on your skill playing.<br><br>At lvl 52 now I can still do main Tank job for anything but the truely godly MOBs there.  My Guild has done raids in Kael Arena where I was the main tank, and we had no deaths.  I have tanked Planes MOBs, I pride myself on being summoned at least once a fight whenever I fight a summoning MOB.  With good gear, and the right gearfor the encounter, a Shadow Knight is not far behind a Warrior in HPs and AC, the difference comes with their disciplines, but unless you only pull 1 MOB an hour, they can't use their disciplines for every fight (people often seem to forget that).  With a good TEAM (it's the whole team that wins fights) you can take most anything as the Main Tank.<br><br>More often though we become pullers.  I can pull better than Monks at my level, because i know how to keep the MOB we want from wandering away before the MOBs we don't leave.  I also have the AC and HPs to take a real beating while getting out of the area so I can feign.  Monks like to pull, and they have brainwashed the unschooled masses of EQ that they are the only ones who should pull, but that is wrong.  I can pull, or be at the tag point in FD mode ready to pick up a MOB and bring it the rest of the way home as well is not better than a Monk, and with my stand-off for pulls, I am less likely to get an add to begin with.<br><br>Agro is where we excell, which is what makes us such a great tank.  I have never had a Cleric get agro's when i was tanking.  My agro is through the roof when that's my job.  In fact ONLY SK's (if they are present) should break mez on any parked MOBs, again I have never had my Chanter get hit when I get the next MOB in line to kill.  Hit them with your 3 debuffs and taunt once in between each and the MOB will ignor the Chante and come right to you.  No one else can do that, NO ONE!  Also once you get the Siphon Life spell you can draw 280 HPs at 1 shot, that will help you when the CHeal is almost there but you need life NOW.  <br><br>I stack every one of my DoTs on the MOBs during raids.  I space them out if I am not main tank, but considering they do a combined 600HPs of damage every application it adds up fast.  we dael damage, it just doesn't spam the screen with hits.  If you debuff and DoT a MOB you have reduced the damage the party will take over-all quite a bit, as the main tank doesn't get hit as hard.<br><br>One last point.  We are the masters of duels, as I'm told.  That has no bearing at all on our usefulness to a group.  fighting another player is completely different than fighting a Named Giant in the Arena of Kael, one has 5k HPs and quads for over 300HPs with rampage, and one hits low and has less that 2k HPs.  Never let dueling confuse you to our strengths (unless you play PvP servers).<br><br>No I'm not in an UBER Guild.  If you are then you will have Twinked lvl 60 warriors that will alway be Main Tank and lvl 60 Monks that will always pull.  For the rest of us, we can Tank and Pull, and ever do significant damage.  Just learn how to play your character to the limits and you'll always have a place on any raid.<br><br>Neptunis<br>lvl 52 DE Reaver</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subje