		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Let me clear up a couple of things about the SK's ability to tank. First off, although it's true that SK's don't quite get the same HP's and AC as warriors, the spells more than make up for that difference.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm running a 36 "untwinked" Troll SK now.  I can easily solo clops and HG's in Rathe Mtns. (How's that for being able to play a tank ?)  It greatly depends on how you use your abilities. Many Warriors would KILL for the ability to FD like a monk.  A decent 2hd slash weapon is all you need, weaponwise. Many of the SK's spells are for the "unexpected" situation. For example, suppose you're getting your butt kicked by a critter that "gets lucky"... If you fear them away, you can buy a few seconds to zone out and heal.  That makes the difference between life and death.  Same thing goes for FD.  It's the variety and overall use of one's abilities that you have to take into consideration.  Cast a 45 HP lifedraw on most opponents in the middle of melee and watch them drop like a stone.  That ability is superior to a warr's kick.  Although a monk is also a toe-to-toe fighter, you're average damage (esp if you play a large race) buries the monk and rogue in sheer power.  If you play a Troll or Iksar, then after a nasty combat all you'd need to do is sit and heal. In 4-5 minutes, you're ready to take on another opponent.  No other race/class combo is as effective at doing this. SK's are truely a great class ! <br><br>Marrowcrusher Sithlyrd <br>36 Troll Shadow Knight<br>Quellious server</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cell